    "image_text_iRgFhW": {
      "type": "image_text",
      "blocks": {
        "bl_text_EL64jY": {
          "type": "bl_text",
          "settings": {
            "col_dk": "12",
            "col_tb": "12",
            "text_size": "40,15",
            "txt_align": "start",
            "sub_heading": "",
            "heading": "",
            "text": "<h2>The Look: A Belted Saree with Tribal Flavor</h2><p></p><p>We styled the saree by:</p><ul><li>Draping the lower half like a <strong>wrap skirt</strong>, keeping it short and practical<br/><br/></li><li>Bringing the pallu over one shoulder in a <strong>thick fold</strong>, then looping it around the neck and back over the opposite shoulder — mimicking the <strong>shoulder wrap</strong> seen in tribal attire<br/><br/></li><li>Adding a <strong>wide leather belt</strong> at the waist to secure the drape and define the shape<br/><br/></li><li>Accessorizing with <strong>beaded earrings</strong>, chunky bangles, and a braided hair crown for texture</li></ul><p>Footwear? We went for <strong>flat leather sandals</strong> — grounded and earthy.<br/><br/></p>",
            "subhd_color": "#222222",
            "hd_color": "#222222",
            "des_color": "#878787",
            "use_shadow": false,
            "button_label": "Button label",
